The paper discusses feature learning algorithms for domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning. The focus is on linear classifiers, which suggests that the paper may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions applications such as image classification and text classification, which are often associated with computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper includes theoretical analysis of the proposed algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
